docs.lead_paragraph: The abortion issue has put members of Congress who support abortion rights in a quandary over the health care legislation. Do they stick to their longstanding principles and fiercely resist the legislative effort to limit access to insurance for abortions?

headline.main: Another Standoff May Be Looming On Abortion Issue

docs.abstract: Members of Congress who support abortion rights are in quandary over health care legislation as they consider potential trade-off between abortion rights and coverage of women's broader health needs; are facing tough choice between resisting efforts to limit access to health insurance for abortions and supporting compromise legislation that could greatly improve health care for women in other ways (M)
